Reasoning: The paper deals with word embeddings, which are a common resource in Natural Language Processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also proposes a new method for improving the quality of cross-lingual embeddings, which involves a non-orthogonal transformation. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which deal with machine learning techniques and AI applications, respectively. Additionally, the paper evaluates its method on intrinsic tasks such as dictionary induction and word similarity, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.MM (Multimedia), which deal with information retrieval and multimedia analysis, respectively.
